race.comment: VIASAIN (3) was a smart winner first up as favourite at Kyneton, okay in a stronger race at Sandown Lakeside last time. Has been kept fresh for this with 31 days between. This looks a touch easier, especially with a key scratching. He can atone. ARABELLA STAR (9) is going very well this time in, dominant at Gawler two back in a Class 1, good again behind Declared at Murray Bridge who was well backed at Caulfield on Saturday. Expect she measures up. THAILESS (5) struggles to win but is going okay and maps for every chance. Expect him to look likely at some stage. SURPRISATIC (4) can be hitting the line late.
